other_tests.findings: The thyroid is unremarkable. The airways are patent to the subsegmental level. There is bibasilar atelectasis. There is an area of probable round atelectasis in the left lower lobe, but an underlying consolidation cannot be ruled out. The heart and pericardium are unremarkable. The aorta and pulmonary arteries are well opacified. There is no pulmonary embolism in the main, right, left, lobar, or segmental pulmonary arteries. The liver appears fatty.
